fields.title: If you wake up looking like this! ...Don't go to work!
fields.content: Known by a slew of names including the common woolly bat and HardwickeÆs forest bat, HardwickeÆs woolly bat looks like it belongs in a horror film. This bat, which resides in parts of Asia and China, usually lives in the forest understory, building its home in hollow trees and piles of dead leaves. While little is known about the Hardwicke woolly bat, scientists have recently noticed these creatures roosting above the digestive fluids within carnivorous plants"

fields.title: Blobfish Voted World's Ugliest Animal
fields.content:
The blobfish is officially the ugliest animal on the planet.

The endangered deep-sea creature, dubbed a "marine Jabba the Hut" by the Guardian, was voted the world's most hideous animal as part of an online competition conducted by the Ugly Animal Preservation Society.

"For too long the cute and fluffy animals have taken the limelight and now hundreds of species are tragically extinct because they were painfully ugly,"

fields.title: Botox Anyone?
fields.content: This little kitten is only young but definitely has not aged well!! He is super wrinkly and his ears look far too big for his tiny head. We just want to give this poor cat a tub of anti-wrinkle cream and a jumper!

fields.title: The Woolly Bat - Love it's cute flower nose
fields.content: Known by a slew of names including the common woolly bat and HardwickeÆs forest bat, HardwickeÆs woolly bat looks like it belongs in a horror film. This bat, which resides in parts of Asia and China, usually lives in the forest understory, building its home in hollow trees and piles of dead leaves. While little is known about the Hardwicke woolly bat, scientists have recently noticed these creatures roosting above the digestive fluids within carnivorous plants

fields.title: All squeak, no bite: The common Mudpuppy
fields.content: This description is of the common mudpuppy, and true to its name, it is an adorable lake-loving creature found here in the Midwest. ItÆs not a dog, it canÆt bark and it doesnÆt enjoy a good tummy rub, but this rare and majestic salamander is wonderfully unique and captivatingly cute.

fields.title: Persian - Strike A Pose
fields.content: We think this little guy is literally hilarious! He has just had a kitty hair cut and he is feeling fab, this cat has so much sass but we canÆt help but laugh at his pompom tail and mustache.

fields.title: Hermit Ibis
fields.content: Hermit ibis (Geronticus eremita) is a very rare colonial bird. We can observe these species in: Arid and semi-arid areas; as well as pastures and fields. The feed of the hermit ibis consists of invertebrates and insects. It is a bird that reaches a length of 70 to 80 centimeters.
